<br>
For all of you PoG-defiling paladins who are planning on recovering your faction by feeding Pandos a billion muffins--forget it. <br>
If you're KoS in PoG, you're KoS to Pandos.<br>
<br>
After several days of fun-filled defoliation in PoG, I visited Pandos--he was warmly. Several days of PoG, mind you. Two days later, after having visited PoG for a single 3 hour stretch--he scowls. Strange. <br>
Sooo, I killed him to see what faction hit he actually was:<br>
FeydarksChampions<br>
ClericsofTunare<br>
SoldiersofTunare<br>
All down. These, along with ServantsofTunare and ProtectorsofGrowth are the hits you take in PoG.<br>
While the Pandos quest gives + hits for these faction,<br>
he was, apparently, not on these factions himself at one time. Now he is.<br>
Neriak red wine invis trick? Won't work. <br>
Pandos is lvl 30ish and will agro on you as soon as you open a trade window regardless of your level.<br>
Now the kicker, I brought a high level enchanter along (who is also KoS from PoG) who the highest level chanter Alliance spell--Collaboration I think it was? He REMAINED KOS! I've never seen a more boggled chanter. This spell is supposed to be a no-fail spell that makes the target's faction non-kos. Yet he remained KoS to him. He tried to charm Pandos--successful, but the muffins give xp but no faction change.<br>
Also, a druid friend spent TWO DAYS in CB laying waste, trying to up her faction. She remains KoS.<br>
My point--beware PoG. If you go KoS to the above factions, you may remain so for life.<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I have found a way around this, but it is very time consuming.<br>
Have the enchanter charm him, bring him to a zone, now while charmed hand him the 4 stacks of 4 muffins (charmed mobs don't give faction hits) and get an invis. <br>
Now have the enchanter zone, thus mob inst mezzed, you are invis causing the indifferent faction, so hit trade, tada faction hits, have a 3rd non-kos person there to hail him and keep on place till the enchanter zones back and charms again. <br>
Rinse. <br>
Repeat. <br>
