<br>
<br>
One last note: that post said the enchanter faction spell series (alliance, benevolence, collaboration, etc.) is supposed to &quot;bring your faction to indifferent&quot;.  This is not correct.  These spells just *raise* your faction from whatever it was.  If you were indifferent before, it would raise you to amiable or warmly.  If you were dubious it might raise you to Apprehensive or indiff.  But unless you're just barely KOS, these spells won't help.  Because once your faction hits Scowling, it doesn't stop there.  The rating gap for Scowling is very wide.<br>
<br>
Here's an example.  Let's use some arbitary numbers to explain factions:<br>
<br>
indiffient = -10 to 10<br>
apprehensive = -30 to -10<br>
dubious = -50 to -30<br>
threatening = -70 to -50<br>
Scowling = -200 to -70<br>
<br>
Okay, I pulled these numbers out of thin air, but it's meant to explain how I believe the faction system works.  If you're at -180 on this list, even the most powerful faction-raising spell will still leave you in the Scowling range.<br>
